Definition: In this task you get a list of integers. You should remove all integers that are divisible by 3 from the list. If every integer in the input list is divisible by 3, then an empty list should be returned. Zero is divisible by 3.

Positive Examples.explanation: 240 and 330 are removed from the list because they are divisible by 3.
Every value in the input list is divisible by 3 so an empty list is returned.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output contains only the integers that are divisible by 3 from the input.
The output only included one instance of the element 497, even though it appears two times in the input list.
